x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">A toxic combination=
 of short sellers and the nattering nabobs of negativism have really got th=
eir hooks into the Warner Bros. Discovery stock these days. It=E2=80=99s no=
w trading below $7 a share, around the all-time low, and down a whopping 15=
 percent in the last week. Overall, the stock is down <i>73 percent</i> sin=
ce <b>David Zaslav</b>=E2=80=99s Hollywood experiment began, in April 2022,=
 and the company=E2=80=99s enterprise value is around $55 billion, 45 perce=
nt less than the $100 billion Zaz paid for WarnerMedia alone. As my partner=
 <b>Matt Belloni</b> <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9p=
ZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dSVXl4aFU5eUtfUXJqbGNHSk5MQT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR=
